            <scopecontent>
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                                 <p>This collection contains a few letters, documents, and manuscripts written by, or relating to, George Johnson Barrett (1818-1876) of Pittsfield, Ill., an itinerant Methodist clergyman. His life is briefly sketched in Irving Dilliard&#039;s remembrance of his son, the Lincoln collector, who no doubt cherished his father&#039;s story of meeting Lincoln. See &quot;Oliver Rogers Barrett, 1873-1950,&quot; <emph render="italic">Journal of the Illinois State Historical Society</emph>, 43 (Autumn 1950), 172-73, and Douglas L. Wilson and Rodney O. Davis, ed., <emph render="italic">Lincoln&#039;s Informants...</emph> (1998), 436.</p>
                                 <p>This collection of the Rev. Barrett&#039;s papers came to the Library in 2014 from Clarendon Van Norman, Jr., who acquired them from the Oliver Barrett auction.</p>
                        </scopecontent>
            


